{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> ἐκ-τρίβω</b> [ῑ], <br /> <i>future</i> <i>passive</i> <b>-τρῐβήσομαι</b>[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Oedipus Tyrannus” 428 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]:—<b>rub out</b>, i. e. <b>produce by rubbing</b>, πῦρ ἔκ τινος [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Institutio Cyri (Cyropaedia)” 2.2.15; φλόγα 2nd c.AD(?): Pollianus Epigrammaticus 9.155 (but in 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Philoctetes” 296 ἐν πέτροισι πέτρον ἐκτρίβων.. ἔφην᾽ ἄφαντον φῶς\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>] <b>rubbing hard</b>): <i>metaphorically</i>, λύπην [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st-2nd c.AD: Plutarchus Biographus et Philosophus 2.610b \">Refs 1st c.AD+</a>]:—<i>passive</i>, τὰ ψυχικὰ προτερήματα διὰ τὰ ἔπαθλα οἷον ἐκτρίβεται [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 3rd c.AD: Longinus Rhetor 44.3. \">Refs 3rd c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> <b>rub out</b>, i.e. <b>to destroy root and branch</b>, σφέας πίτυος τρόπον ἀπείλεε ἐκτρίψειν (compare πίτυς) [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 6.37; ἐ. τινὰ πρόρριζον 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Hippolytus” 684; τὴν ποίην ἐκ τῆς γῆς ἐκτρίβειν 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 4.120; αὕτη μ᾽ ἡ γυνή ποτ᾽ ἐκτρίψει 3rd c.BC: Herodas Mimographus 6.27, uncertain in 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Cyclops” 475 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; βίον ἐ. <b>bring</b> life <b>to a wretched end</b>, = Latin <i>conterere vitam</i>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Oedipus Tyrannus” 248, compare 428 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]:—<i>passive</i>, πρόρριζος ἐκτέτριπται [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 6.86 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>].; ὁπλὰς ἐκτετριμμένος with the hoofs <b>worn off</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.AD: Lucianus Sophista “Asin.” 19. \">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__III</b></Level2> <b>rub constantly, wear out</b>, Ἄτλας.. νώτοις οὐρανὸν ἐκτρίβων [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Ion” 2 (assuming variant). \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__IV</b></Level2> <b>rub, thresh out</b>, <i>falsa lectio</i> in [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.BC: Nicander Epicus “fragment” 68.3. \">Refs 2nd c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__V</b></Level2> <b>polish</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-3rd c.BC: Theophrastus Philosophus “Historia Plantarum” 4.11.6, 2nd c.BC: Polybius Historicus 10.20.2; ἀργυρώματα “Class.Phil.” 19.234 (3rd c.BC)\">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]; compare ἐξετρίβετο· σφόδρα ἐκοσμεῖτο, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.AD(?): Hesychius Legal icographus \">Refs 5th c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__V.2</b></Level3> <b>wipe out</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 3rd c.BC: Herodas Mimographus 1.79. \">Refs 3rd c.BC+</a>]","strongNumber":"G7160","accentedUnicode":"ἐκτρίβω","shortDef":"to obliterate; scour","mediumDef":"to obliterate; scour","stepGloss":"to obliterate","stepTransliteration":"ektribō","count":0,"_step_Type":"verb"}]}